de.oaam.model.oaam.restrictions

Interface PowerSourceRestriction

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DeviceRestrictionA, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, ModeDependentElementA, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA, SignalGroupRestrictionA, SignalRestrictionA, SubfunctionRestrictionA, TaskGroupRestrictionA, TaskRestrictionA, VariantDependentElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    PowerSourceRestrictionImpl

    public interface PowerSourceRestriction
extends TaskRestrictionA, TaskGroupRestrictionA, SignalRestrictionA, SignalGroupRestrictionA, SubfunctionRestrictionA, DeviceRestrictionA, OaamBaseElementA, VariantDependentElementA, ModeDependentElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Power Source Restriction'. A power restriction forces functions or signals to be mapped or not mapped to devices with a certain power supply.

    The following features are supported:

    • Power Source Name
    • Is Forbidden
    • Power Sources
    See Also:
    RestrictionsPackage.getPowerSourceRestriction()
